      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That makes sense. So if the COGS goes up because of the lost stock, the turnover ratio drops. Can you give me a quick example with some numbers? Like if we had $500k in COGS normally, but the shrinkage added $75k to that, and our average inventory was $100k, what would the ratio look like compared to before?",
